{"name":"Turkey Mulligatawny Soup","slug":"turkey-mulligatawny-soup","description":"When the temp drops, there’s no better way to warm up than with a steaming bowl of hearty soup. And, even better, this one is a smart way to make the most of your leftover turkey! Turn those turkey morsels into a high-protein, hearty dish.","ingredients":[{"name":"large onion","quantity":"1","additionalInstruction":"diced"},{"name":"large carrot","quantity":"1","additionalInstruction":"diced"},{"name":"curry powder","quantity":"2 tbsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Vegetable Broth or Nourish Broth","quantity":"4 cups","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Vegetable Broth Mix","quantity":"1 <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> tsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"boiling water","quantity":"1 cup","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Nourish Broth Mix","quantity":"1 <sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> tsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"boiling water","quantity":"1 cup","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"diced tomatoes","quantity":"1 can (14 oz /398 ml)","additionalInstruction":"drained"},{"name":"cooked leftover turkey","quantity":"1 lb (450 g)","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"uncooked long grain white rice","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub> cup","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Granny Smith apple","quantity":"1","additionalInstruction":"peeled, cored and diced"},{"name":"lemon juice","quantity":"2 tsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"plain low-fat yogurt","quantity":"<sup>1</sup>&frasl;<sub>4</sub> cup","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Sea Salt","quantity":null,"additionalInstruction":"to taste"}],"totalTime":"40 - 45 min","servings":"6 servings","preparation":["Heat Multipurpose Pot to medium. With spray pump, lightly coat bottom of pot with vegetable oil. Sauté onions and carrots for about 6 minutes, or until they begin to soften.","Sprinkle curry powder over vegetables; stir well and cook until aromatic, about 1 minute. Add broth, tomatoes, cooked turkey and rice. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.","When rice is almost tender, add apple with lemon juice and simmer uncovered 10 more minutes.","Ladle into individual bowls and top with a dollop of low-fat yogurt and salt on the side."],"tags":[{"slug":"low_sodium","name":"Low-sodium"},{"slug":"sugar_conscious","name":"Sugar Conscious"},{"slug":"one_dish","name":"One Dish"},{"slug":"dinner","name":"Dinner"},{"slug":"lunch","name":"Lunch"},{"slug":"gluten_free_e8446d0","name":"Gluten-free"},{"slug":"high_protein","name":"High Protein"},{"slug":"sides","name":"Side Dishes"},{"slug":"chicken___poultry","name":"Chicken & Poultry"}],"nutritionalInformation":{"servingSize":"","calories":300,"fat":3.5,"saturatedFat":1,"transFat":0,"cholesterol":95,"sodium":380,"carbohydrate":30,"fiber":3,"sugars":8,"protein":43},"tips":[],"perfectlyBalanceYourPlate":"","imagePath":"../images/Turkey-Mulligatawny-Soup_1036x583.jpg","products":[{"slug":"vegetable_broth_mix","name":"Vegetable Broth Mix"},{"slug":"nourish_broth_mix","name":"Nourish Broth Mix"}]}